│                                                                                        │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                            │
│                                                                                        │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                                        │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                            │
│ The deadargelim pass crashes on a module containing musttail calls. The verifier       │
│ reports two musttail violations after running -passes=deadargelim:                     │
│ - cannot guarantee tail call due to mismatched return types (for a musttail call to    │
│ @B)                                                                                    │
│ - musttail call must precede a ret with an optional bitcast (for a musttail call to    │
│ @F38)                                                                                  │
│ This indicates that the pass changed function signatures (particularly return types)   │
│ in the presence of musttail, breaking musttail's strict requirements.                  │
│                                                                                        │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                                │
│ The log shows the verifier errors immediately, meaning the final IR after deadargelim  │
│ is invalid. No other debug-only logs are available, but based on the pass code,        │
│ deadargelim can change function return types (remove dead return components) and       │
│ updates all direct call sites. It also reconstructs aggregate returns at call sites by │
│ inserting extractvalue/insertvalue around call results when return types change.       │
│                                                                                        │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                                │
│ - In surveyFunction(), the pass carefully avoids removing arguments if the function    │
│ has musttail callers (HasMustTailCallers) or contains musttail calls itself            │
│ (HasMustTailCalls). However, it does not similarly protect return values. As a result, │
│ it may decide to eliminate/alter return values of a function that has musttail callers │
│ or musttail calls.                                                                     │
│ - In removeDeadStuffFromFunction(), when a callee's return type changes, the pass      │
│ rewrites all callers. For non-void changes, it synthesizes IR                          │
│ (insertvalue/extractvalue) to rebuild the old aggregate type at the call site. If a    │
│ call site is a musttail call, inserting any instruction between the musttail call and  │
│ the ret breaks musttail's rule that the musttail call must be immediately followed by  │
│ a ret returning (optionally via a bitcast) the call value. This explains the second    │
│ verifier error on the F36→F38 musttail path.                                           │
│ - Additionally, changing a function's own return type in the presence of a musttail    │
│ call result being returned directly (e.g., C returning result of musttail to B)        │
│ creates a mismatch between the musttail call's return type and the function's return   │
│ type, producing the first “cannot guarantee tail call due to mismatched return types”  │
│ error.                                                                                 │
│ - The comment in surveyFunction() says: "If we have any returns of musttail results -  │
│ the signature can't change". The code sets HasMustTailCalls for terminating musttail   │
│ calls, but only uses that flag to force arguments live, not return values. That is the │
│ gap.                                                                                   │
│                                                                                        │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s)                                                              │
│ File: llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/DeadArgumentElimination.cpp                              │
│ Insertion after line 616 (right after logging HasMustTailCallers):                     │
│                                                                                        │
│ Add the following block to force all return values live when either the function has   │
│ musttail callers or contains musttail calls:                                           │
│                                                                                        │
│ {                                                                                      │
│   // If this function has musttail callers or contains a terminating musttail          │
│   // call, we cannot change its return type without violating musttail rules.          │
│   // Mark all return values live to prevent signature changes.                         │
│   if (HasMustTailCallers || HasMustTailCalls) {                                        │
│     for (unsigned Ri = 0; Ri != RetCount; ++Ri) {                                      │
│       RetValLiveness[Ri] = Live;                                                       │
│       MaybeLiveRetUses[Ri].clear();                                                    │
│     }                                                                                  │
│   }                                                                                    │
│ }                                                                                      │
│                                                                                        │
│ This is placed just before the code that records return-value liveness into            │
│ LiveValues:                                                                            │
│   // Now we've inspected all callers, record the liveness of our return values.        │
│   for (unsigned Ri = 0; Ri != RetCount; ++Ri)                                          │
│     markValue(createRet(&F, Ri), RetValLiveness[Ri], MaybeLiveRetUses[Ri]);            │
│                                                                                        │
│ Rationale:                                                                             │
│ - Ensures functions with musttail callers or musttail returns won't have their return  │
│ type changed, avoiding both kinds of musttail verifier failures:                       │
│   - Mismatched caller/callee return types for musttail sites.                          │
│   - Extra instructions between musttail call and ret introduced by aggregate           │
│ reconstruction.                                                                        │
│ - Matches the intent of the comment "the signature can't change" and mirrors the       │
│ existing protection that prevents argument removal under these conditions.             │
│                                                                                        │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                         │
│ The crash is caused by deadargelim changing return types in the presence of musttail,  │
│ which requires exact signature and immediate ret constraints. By marking all return    │
│ values live for functions that either have musttail callers or contain (terminating)   │
│ musttail calls, we prevent signature changes that would violate musttail requirements. │
│ This preserves correctness without broadening the pass's impact beyond necessary       │
│ constraints and aligns with existing handling for arguments under musttail conditions. │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                                        │
│                                                                                        │
